Workout was 7 miles marathon pace, 1 mile tempo, 5 mile marathon, 1 mile temp.  Head wind for the first 7.  John was struggling so I started to drop him after the first mile, but decided after 3 it would be better to run with him the rest of the way out then push on the turnaround.  Out in 42:51 (6:02).  At the turnaround I went hard on the first tempo and really didn't let up for the next 7 miles.  Tempos were 5:28 and 5:23.  Had to force myself to slow down for the marathon pace.  Ended up back in 38:39 (5:31).  The last 200-400 were into the wind otherwise I think I could have hit the teens.  Note: Out was 7.1 miles because I looped back for John.  Also, had a few dogs run in front of us.  These dogs are begging to get kicked.  

Really happy with how my legs responded.  Now off to an ice bath.

The 20, 15, 10, 5 workout from a few weeks ago.  This time I remembered to charge the GPS.  Wasn't completely warmed up at first so I started slow.  Distances (paces) were 3.6 (5:34), 2.77 (5:26), 1.88 (5:20), 1 (5:10).  I decided to finish the mile on the last interval.  


This workout was a little slower than the last time I did it, but this time I was coming into it with a lot more mileage.  I would also say my effort level was much lower.  I didn't kill any one of those intervals.  My biggest challenge right now is that the area between too fast and too easy is really small right now.  I feel like I can go for forever at 5:40 right now, but at 5:25 I'm working really hard.

5.25 up. 5 down.  Pretty quality warmup and cooldown.  Cooldown was a loop around Burke Lake.  Warmup was random.  Took a while to get going because of tired legs, but felt like I was actually warmed up for a race for once.

Burke Lake 12k race.  Pretty cold morning so I debated tights vs shorts and went with shorts.  I think that was a good decision.  Goal for today was to win the race in a solid time, but not damage my legs to the point that I couldn't do 23 miles today.  I think I accomplished both goals.  John and I sat on two guys for the first mile then i decided the pace was slow (high 5:30s) so I took the lead.  I could still hold a full conversation at 3 miles when John and I surged to drop 3rd place.  Coming over the dam I dropped John and was on my own from the turnaround on.  I dropped the pace a bit when I turned around (out in 20:35, back in 20:10) but at no point was the race that hard.  I didn't kick to much just tried to focus on turnover at the end and dropped the pace to around 5:05 for the last 400m.  I'm calling this a tempo because I think I had another 5-10 seconds a mile in the bank if I had been pushed.  Next weekend I'll test myself a bit more.

Ran to and from my soccer game.  That was around 3 miles.  I'm logging the game as 1.9 and rationalizing it as striders because otherwise I'd be going back outside for another 1.9 miles and that doesn't seem like a good decision.  Legs are tired, but I think they are doing okay.  I'm hoping playing soccer and ultimate will start to give me some speed again.
Went skiing at Wisp and didn't get a run in.  Wisp was fairly flat in a lot of parts so I got a decent amount of cross country skiing in.  Arms and legs quite sore.  Abs and hip routine x 20

Ran to Fort Dupont on the Fort Circle trail.  The path was pretty wet from rain earlier in the day, but it was nice to get on trails.  Legs still sore from Sunday.
2 up, 1.5 down

*6:15pm

really great tempo.  Heavy wind the whole way out.  Went out for 26 minutes then back in a little under 24.  On the way out my HR was under 160, gradually increased the effort until I hit the mid 160s for the last mile.  John stayed with me the whole time which was nice.  I probably would have slowed down the last couple miles if he hadn't hung with me.
5:49, 5:46, 5:51, 5:54, .8 mile turnaround section, 5:25, 5:21, 5:27, 5:14

This workout was the same average pace at the 40 minute tempo I did 6 weeks ago.  I think the temperature was about the same, but the wind was worse today.  Also, I was wearing heavier shoes today and running on the towpath.  I'd say I could hit 5:30 for this under ideal conditions with a tempo effort.  

Encouraged by the faster pace for the last mile.  I need to be more comfortable at quicker paces.  I'll probably try to throw in a few quicker miles on the workout this weekend.
Ran home via bk.  Pretty sore from yesterday so I was moving pretty slow at times
Ran to work.  Played squash. Then ran to the metro.
ran to the wizards game.  Feared the brow.  Ran home.

Run to the metro and back with a game of ultimate in the middle.  We crushed the team we played 15-5 so I didn't have to run as much as in some games.  However, I played 15 points and popped in zone for most of them.
6.25 up, 1.75 down.  Ended up walking a bit after we finished the workout so the cooldown was short.

Workout was 2 x 5 @marathon + 1 @ tempo.  I was feeling tired from Ultimate and John doesn't like these workouts much so we decided not to push the marathon pace work.  We were in the the mid 5:50s on the way out.  Pushed a tempo mile (5:00ish) then hit 6:00-6:10 for the next 5 miles.  Last mile hurt but managed a 5:21.  Heart rate was pretty low on the marathon pace stuff 150, but it got up to 169 on the tempos.  By the end I was tightening up quite a bit.  I think it was mostly because I needed to eat.  I think my policy is going to be I bring something to eat when I go over 20 miles.

Ran with John.  Really slow run through Rock Creek.  Ran down the Park rd trails the long way then came back on the bike path.  Finished up Harvard Road.  We hit a decent pace on the bike path, but I think we were so slow in the trails that I'm still assuming a slow pace.
Ran Andrea's Georgetown Standard.  Light headed for most of it.  I guess i should have eaten more this afternoon.  Hoping that I'll have recovered enough to have at least one decent run tomorrow.

Treadmill run at the Census.  Was going to do 4-5, but my legs were just exhausted.  Plan was to run in the afternoon, but I didn't make it out before it started raining so I basically took an off day.  Not that worried because I'm getting a ton of miles on Tuesday.  I'll just need to make sure I double a lot the second half of the week.
Morning run to work.  Running with a drawstring bag the whole way so nothing spectacular.  I think my legs have recovered enough for a workout tonight.
9.75 up, 4.5 down

2 x 1 mile then 1 x .75.

Was supposed to be a really hard factorial tempo, but my legs were dead and there was a really heavy headwind so we pushed that workout back.  Ran out to mile 4 then ran the repeats with the wind.  Didn't feel like the wind was as strong on the way back.  Really happy with the turnover I was getting.  I could have done 5 x 1 mile under 5 with the wind which is a good sign.  Ran home past John's work.
Morning run at the Census
Ran home from softball

Ran hills with John after work.  Home to the West side of Rock Creek.  Ran the uphills hard and the flat/downhills medium pace.  Was wearing half tights under tights which was really constricting.  John had a better workout than I did, but mine was still pretty good.
Morning run to the FRB.  Legs a bit sore.
Ran home from the Census.  Census, Penn Ave, N. to RFK, H St, NJ to FL.  Hitting really good paces, but the run was really broken up by lights.

Tempo Long Run.  Ended up doing:
3.25 wu (23 min)
3.6   T   (20min)
9.3   E   (65min)
3.85 T   (20min)
2.5   cd  (18min)

There was a break in the middle of the 9.3 to get gu and water at a GNC.  I decided I don't like GNCs.  HR on the tempos was about 160 on average.  HR was pretty consistent between the two tempos.  First one was a net uphill, second a net downhill.  Plus it was warmer on the second.  Feeling pretty good about the shape I'm in now.  The second tempo started at 5:18 on a downhill mile and I dropped the pace to 5:00 by the end.  That's something I would do in college so its nice to be able to do it once again.

Run to frisbee then two games and a little running home. My total running was probably closer to 6 miles for all of this, but I'm discounting it because it wasn't continuous. However, it was 4 hours of excersize so I feel like I have to log something. My legs felt good for the games, but I didn't eat/drink enough after the games and my body started to shut down. Ultimate seems to be doing good things for me. I'm getting more explosive now.
run at the census then softball then home from softball
ran with Andrea from her home.  slow run in the cold.

blind fartek with jake for the middle 10 miles.  We did the Wednesday Mastik route in 60 minutes.  we were taking turns leading intervals for .5-5 minutes.  It was a good stretch out workout and we got to 5:40 pace on multiple miles.
Ran with Jake.  4 striders and hurdle drills
Run from Andrea's.  Felt exhausted so I cut it short and walked a hill.
to the metro, twinbrook to the car and back, home from the metro

south along the mississippi at 7am.  Out in 35 back in 34.

Great day for racing.Needed to run 53 minutes or better to qualify for Pacers elite races so mission accomplished.  Went out a little aggressively, had a bad 4th mile, then a few slowish miles into the wind on Hanes point.  pulled it back together for a solid last two miles to hit my goal time.  First race since coming back that I'm really happy with.  Need to improve my VO2 and lift a little more

roosevelt island run

4 mile warmup then 3 x 2 miles hardish with John.  Both of us still had dead legs so we didn't push too hard.  Times were 11:45, 11:40, 10:57 (5:05 last mile).  I opened up for that last mile to see what I could do.  Turns out my legs still have some pop in them.  I want to do that more often just to get my legs used to going faster than 10 mile pace.
post softball run with Andrea.  We checked out the cherry blossoms then ran home.  Feeling a little tired, but overall not doing too bad.
Run home, short break, reverse of the park road loop.  Felt pretty good.  Moving well for a good part of the run.

9:15am - LSD

Out late last night so didn't make it up for the SLR.  Yogurt and granola for breakfast then hit the roads.  Went Park road trails the the trails along beach drive until I hit 50 mins.  Came back the same way except I left RCP at Calvert.  Legs pretty tight when I started.  I'm thinking the planks I did on Thursday were getting my hip flexors and hamstrings.  Started rolling a bit for the last 5, but no part of the run was particularly fast.

2 miles for 2 games of ultimate.  I'm very convinced that is a gross underestimate so I don't feel bad about it.

3 miles at the GMU track meet.  Over half was barefoot.

Took a knee to my quad during frisbee today.  It is pretty knotted right now.  I'm hoping I can work the knot out in the morning.

12:00 - Long Run

Ran with John on the Towpath.  Legs pretty sore including a tight quad from yesterday so we took it easy.  Started tightening up at the end which slowed the pace a bit.  Trying to recover now to get ready for soccer and the second run of the day.

Ran to soccer with Andrea.  Feeling pretty tired, but I managed to pull off a good game.  Scored out first two goals one header one volley then got the second assist on our other goal.  Ran home at a decent clip.  Legs tired and really hungry, but no injuries to report.
Run to work in the morning with a bag.  Tired and sore.
Ran home then Park to Calvert with Andrea.  Met up with John in RCP.  Tired and sore again, but I think I should be good to go tomorrow.

12:00 - Easy Run
Once again pretty tired.  Holding higher mileage after a big weekend is proving to be tough.  Nothing is injured, but I'm not breaking any land speed records.  I think I'm going to do the 3k Tidal Basin race tomorrow.  I'll probably go out in 4:45-4:50 with the wind and try to hold on coming back.  I need to get ready for the fast first mile at the Parkway Classic.

ran the 1500-3k double at the tidal basin races.  I was the fastest person there by far so the entire race was alone.  1500 I went out in a comfortable 3:16, lost a few seconds on the turnaround, and came back a little faster.  3k I was out in 4:40 something which means I was pretty even.  I didn't push for time too hard on either of them because I'm going to do an actual workout tomorrow.  This was a chance to stretch the legs and make sure my quad was healed.  It isn't 100 percent, but it doesn't hurt running so I'm not going to back off at all.
run home after softball.  we lost the game in the bottom of the 7th.  not happy about that.

Home from work.

running twin lakes with Andrea after dinner.  I was really full and tired from earlier in the day so the run was pretty miserable.  We just stopped early because I wasn't having any fun.

Run from Manor Oaks.  Did the Hilty, Farm rd, Wiestertown loop, but did that subdivision on the left instead of the hill by the park.  It adds a little bigger hill and about half a mile I think.  Was pretty dead by the end.  It was heating up and I was really hungry.
Morning run to CVS to get a razor and notebook.  Didn't have time to get in any more distance.
Ran with Petro from Boom Island Park.  I'd eaten a lot right before the run so I wasn't feeling great at the beginning, but started rolling on the way back.  Really good run.

Moving today so not much of a run.  Ran to UMN from home.  Then bussed to Aehle's to get my bike.  Biked to Emily's then home which was probably 10 miles since I stayed along the river.  Not a bad day of working out.

Biking to and from school twice.  Once was to the athletic center and back.

First run with the UMN running club.  Probably the best quality run I've done since Petro ran with me in early August.  Had fun talking to people about the running club.  I think this will be motivation to keep running.
Bike to the east bank and back

1.75 warmup and cooldown to Riverside Park with the running club.  Ran 6, 6, 6, 4, 2, 1 mins with 1 min rest between each interval.  Don't know anything about paces, but high 5's feels about right.  I was definitely running out of gas towards the end, but I still managed to maintain my position in the pack.  Started at the back on the first one and moved into the top 7 by the end.  At one point I was top 4, but I ended up losing them when they decided to jog hard on the segment between intervals.  Pretty happy with how things went given my training.  Think I should be a solid top 5 in a week or two.
Morning run around the neighborhood.  Right hamstring sore and both calves sore as well.  Pretty quick turnaround after the evening workout.
ran with Jake north on the Mississippi in the dark.  Out in 23 and back in 20-21.
2 mile warmup to run with the running club.  4 x 2 mile at riverside park.  6 minute rest between. 10:58,11:06,:11:08,11:03 Was leading the second group.
Ran with Jake in the cold rain.  We only ran to the river and back because it was late and raining hard.  I was sore from the workout anyway so it wasn't a bad idea to take it easy.
Ran to watch the the twin cities marathon.

ran with Gjoraas and Jake.  raining on the run and not particularly fast.
midtown greenway down to minnehaha ave back past lake hiawatha.  My longest run since the marathon.  Legs sore for the rest of the day.
Ran the same route as Thursday except I walked the bridge and cut off a little on the west bank.  Tired but doing okay.
Run in the cold rain with Jake.  didn't really feel like running today so we didn't go far.
Ran with Jake around 8pm.  Didn't feel great, but kept up with Jake as he pushed the pace.

Ran with Finan for the first time ever.  Him exhausted and me well rested turned out to be the right combination.  Good run although a little embarrassing I've lived here for 3 months and don't have any go to runs between 9 and 11 miles.

Ran with Jake along the river to the falls then back through the neighborhoods instead of minnehaha for some extra distance and so we could do striders at 44th ave.  Felt pretty tired today, but the striders helped a lot.

Ran with Jake at 9:30am.  Ran north to franklin bridge.  Then the bridge north of the U back along the river.  Felt tired but we still clipped off a few miles in the mid 6's.  Trying to start getting more quality miles on my non workout days because I'm not doing enough workouts to need easy days.  played about 15 points of ultimate later and biked 5 miles.

200 meter hills on Franklin.  Same hill I did a month ago in about 45 seconds each.  This time I was running with Dan which meant we were running a pretty active recovery.  I was just trying to hang on by the end, but Dan was pulling away.  Each lap was about 1:35 with 1:31s on both ends.  I was climbing just under 40 to start.  I'd say half were under 40.  the rest were 40-42.  3.3 up, 3.2 down.  Running with Jake for the cooldown and I was exhausted.  Completely carb depleted by the end. Got home and ate and now I feel better.

Ran north with Jake along the West Bank.  Crossed to the east bank north of the UMN bridge and came back on the east side to Franklin where we jumped over the 29th ave.  Good run, but my calves are still sore from Monday.  However, my mileage is the highest its been since before the marathon so its not surprising I'm a little sore.

Guessing on the mileage.  Made it out for a morning run today.  Jumped on the trails heading south from the entrance just north of 32nd st.  Remembered why I run this trail in the other direction when I wiped out by the drain pipe.  I also need to find a better way to connect this trail to the north.  I ended up running up a dry creak to get back on the normal trails which didn't make for a good run.  Glad I was in tights today because the fall skinned up my hands and hip a bit.  They really hurt for a few minutes, but I didn't do any permanent damage.  Right calf still really tight.  Trying to stretch it throughout the day.

with Jake up 29th to midtown greenway to west rive to stone arch and back.  Stopped at the park on the greenway for 4 striders.  Built up speed on each one and ran the last one pretty fast.  Legs felt pretty good.  I'm still surprised by the paces I'm getting.  It seems like we are running faster than what I get when I map things.  It might just be the night running that makes things feel fast, but I thought we'd be closer to 7 min pace. Calf felt fine.  I stretched it a lot today and I guess that helped.

Late run with Jake.  Thursdays are a terrible day for my running.  I have class every 2 hours from 9-7:30 which means I don't get out for a run until 9pm.  It was raining a bit when we finally got out there.  We were moving well for a few miles in the middle, but I think in the dark the slow first and last mile on 32nd st just kill our average pace.

West River Pkwy - Fort Snelling Bridge - East River Pkwy - Lake - 8:05am

Ran with Finan again from my place. Last week this run doubled my mileage for the week and I carried it into a solid week of running.  Apparently all I need for running motivation is to talk about racing.  Knee soreness was gone from last night.  I've now run 8 straight days.  If I'm not careful I might get in decent shape for this thanksgiving day 5k.

3 mile warmup, 3 mile tempo, 3.4 mile cooldown.  Ran with Jake from home.  Warmed up to the Franklin bridge on West River.  Did a strider then started south on a tempo.  Splits were 5:25,5:36,5:33.  Felt pretty easy.  Working harder on the first mile than the other two.  We started to slow on the second so I threw in a surge to get us back on pace.  Definitely could have done another mile at least without the workout being very hard.  Its now 2 hours later and I don't even feel like I ran a workout.  Good sign for things to come.  Afterwards did 5 strides on the soccer field.  Was moving pretty well on each of those as well.

Early run with Jake.  Played two frisbee games later.  We won the bottom half of the of the second division which means we were 13th out of 60ish teams. I've never seen so much terrible ultimate in one place...  Anyway, sore by the end of the day, but nothing too concerning.  First 70 mile monday to sunday week in about 6 months.

7pm. Got out with Jake for a run in the dark. Its going to be pretty much impossible to run in daylight for the next few months. We started off a little slow then picked it up into the mid 6s, but Jake was having stomach issues so we slowed it back down.  First day in new shoes so both our feet were hurting a bit.  Finished with 5 striders in the school's parking lot.  Opened up for the last two and almost hit my top speed.  Going to have to race a 200 at some point to see how fast I can go.

First snow run of the year.  We were right on the edge of the snow rain line.  So we got to get wet at the same time we were getting hit in the face by snow.  Traction wasn't bad though.  I wasn't feeling great today so Jake was kind of dragging me for a decent part of the run.

7:40pm. Started out from the department then met Jake 2.4 in on West River Road. First 2.4 were at about 6 minute pace because I was feeling good and wanted to push a little.  Jake and I were moving pretty well once we joined up to run north to roughly the stone arch bridge.  I kind of messed up the route I wanted to run, but I think in the confusion we ran an extra mile or so which means I have no complaints.  

Feeling pretty good after 2 days with lower mileage.  Going to need a legitimate long run this weekend to make up for light running to start out the week.

This was really 2/3 runs.  Weiwen wanted to run with me to we did 15 minutes from the department at a quite slow pace.  Then I dropped him off and jumped on the west river trails, but I screwed them up and ended up on some bad ones that were not very runnable.  Then took a bus back to school went to micro and ran home.  I was pretty tired today so I didn't push at any point.  Did 4 striders on the soccer field.
Ran down to the dog park with Jake.  Felt pretty good, but kept it under control because of the race tomorrow.
3 up, 2 down.  Jake and I decided we would run again later in the day, but then we ended up not running again.
With Jake after work.  It was pretty cold outside. Felt okay, but don't really like running in the cold.
Similar route to last night but ran the East Bank for a bit.  Balls cold again.

With Jake on the East River hill from the bottom of the washington ave bridge to the stop sign 400 meters away.  We were hitting the hills in 1:25-1:30.  I was trying to hit the bottoms hard and hang on once I got the last 100 and I was pretty successful.  Once of my better workouts this year.  Did 6 hills.
Split run.  Did about 4 before recitation including a couple with the running group then ran home from campus.
Double bridge run with Jake with 4 striders at the end. Ate ethiopian 2 hours before the run and I was really feeling it.

Split tempo with Jake.  15 minutes into the wind at about 5:35 pace.  Then 10 minutes with the wind at 5:15 pace or so.  The way out felt easy until the last half mile when we dropped our pace.  On the way back I was with Jake for the first 5 then he stopped as we'd planned and I kept going for 5 minutes.  Tried to drop the pace after the first mile and got it to 5:04 for the next half mile, but then I started to tire and felt back to 5:15 or so for the mile as a whole.
3.5.  2 up and 1.5 down
With Jake, West bank to UMN and back.
With Ryan and Jake.  Really windy once we turned around.  North on West River again.
Easy run by myself.  Did 4 100m striders at the end.  Feeling some pep in my step.

about 4 up, 8 x hill (around 450 m each with no jog back down on the last one = 6.7k = 4.15 miles), over 3.5 down. Close enough to 12 that I'm calling it 12.

Same hill as last week, but 2 more reps. Last week was 1:35 then a little 1:30 for the rest. This week  started with 2 around 1:34-5 then consistently cut down from 1:29 to 1:27 over the last 5. Last one was around 1:23.  Much better workout than last week considering it was colder, more windy, and I was wearing tights.  Also, I would say this workout took less out of me than last week.
Morning shakeout to pick up my number for the race tomorrow.  Legs were quite sore from last night.

Ran home from the U along the west bank.  Didn't wear a watch so I'm guessing on both mileage and time.  First run with snow on the ground this year although there wasn't much.  I really like the air after a snow.  I don't know why.  Really glad I was only running one direction because that direction was with a pretty strong wind.  Jake did a loop from the apartment at about the same time and enjoyed his run much less than I enjoyed mine.
south into a rough wind back on east bank.  same loop i did with finan a few weeks ago
29th ave to franklin to west river. threw in some intervals.  three between 200 and 400 and on closer to half a mile

2.5 up, 3 miles at 5:30, 2 down.  Ran on the treadmill at UMN.  Peter joined me for the tempo portion.  I think I'm going to try to make this a weekly thing.
Ran with Andrea and Christine. The valley was flooded so we turned around early. It was 60 degrees.
Ran with Andrea for the first three from her place. Went off on my own but it was really hilly and windy so I didn't go that far. I need to start running more.

night run with Jake. On snow and ice so once again not so fast. We're supposed to break freezing next week for the first time in a month. It should feel like summer.
Washington bridge and back. It had just snowed so this was a slow slog. Felt fine. Did some pushups, jump rope, pullups and abs.

Well that was a long one. Wanted to get a longer run with Jake. Longer for me right now is basically anything over 5 miles so this fit the bill. We went west on lake then came back along the minnehaha trail to lake hiawatha. That run is always longer than I think it will be. I really like the route so I keep doing it, but I haven't managed to get myself in shape to do it comfortably. Achilles hurt a little bit two separate times for a minute or two. nothing that affected my stride and I got ice on it 4 times afterwards. I think I'm just going to start running through this a bit and hope it gets better.

Solo run to the river south along the high trails then across at Minnehaha Academy then wound back. Achilles wasn't bad. I iced twice afterwards. Last night's meeting has me motivated to get better from this injury and get back in shape. It has me thinking about goals for this season
1. Sub 16 minute 5k on Memorial Day (Oh how fall I've fallen)
2. Be able to touch my toes when I wake up in the morning
3. Abs 3 days a week
4. 30 Pull ups 
5. 40 Push ups

Obviously I'm focusing on getting some strength and flexibility for the next couple months. I want to get a solid base by the end of June so I can try to crush the fall. The goal for this Spring is to stay healthy and get some mileage under my belt.

6:30pm with with RNF. Jake and I got there late so we had to work a bit to catch up in the first mile. After that settled into a pace around 7 mins the rest of the way. I wish I could say 9 miles at 7 min pace is easy for me right now, but it definitely wasn't. I felt like I was pushing for the second half a little. My HR was probably around 150. I should start wearing my monitor again so I have a better idea. Stretched quite a bit after and got in an ice after we went out to dinner. Achilles was pretty much the same as yesterday.

Started to go for a run but my achilles hurt a little and I wanted to make sure I iced it. Also, I only wanted to run 30 miles this week and I had 27 in the first three days so I figured backing off wasn't a bad deal. Iced 4 times with my new ice trash can.
Easy run with Andrea. We checked out Powderhorn Park. Achilles was bothering me on the turns through the neighborhood. More stretching and icing after.

Wasn't going to run because my achilles was feeling tight, but it was too nice of a day to pass up so I headed out. Ended up doing the double bridge run coming back through the trails. Wasn't feeling great at the beginning, but ended up hitting some high 6's on the way back. Lots of icing after.

Lots of biking today. To school via the greenway. Home via river and the ford bridge. Then to the gym and back for soccer. Also got in some soccer and 2 ices. Started the second week of lifting. I wasn't able to complete the push-ups but everything else went okay. I'm sore but my Achilles seems to be on the mend.

Biked to school today then from school to RnF. That meant I had 11 miles in running before the run and I was definitely feeling it. Turned off early with Kelly for 7ish then we did 8 striders in the street. the good news is that I had no achilles pain today. My left IT band is feeling a little tight in the knee, but I'm basically sore all over right now from the lifting and everything so I'm not that concerned. Hoping that next week I'll be in good enough shape to hang with the top group.
lake to franklin
ran home from school then to dairy queen for a blizzard.
Ran from Minnehaha park towards the dog park. Felt pretty good but my achilles was a little tight.

Log run with Jake. Started towards the river on 32nd into a really strong wind. We thought we were going to be running in a lot of rain, but it was actually pretty nice. Ran the loop through the top of the city to Cedar Lake then back on Lake street because I missed the midtown greenway. Felt roughly as difficult as the long run two weeks ago, but it was a bit longer.
Easy 3 miles shakeout run. Thought I was going easy to be ready for a longer run in the morning, but it turned out I was just going easy because the run with Finan got pushed to Thursday.
Morning run to river road then back on the greenway. Felt much better than yesterday.

Hyland ski with Jake. Deck was hard and pretty fast. We were pretty relaxed until the end where we dropped it under 6. Added the first section of the scenic foothills to our loop. My v1 was looking better but I was having trouble holding the v2 on the hard snow.

home - Lake bridge - franklin bridge - 29th ave

Slow first mile. Picked it up for a mile or two in the middle and got it under 7, but then backed off for the last bit. Apparently I backed off quite a bit because the average pace was really slow.

Ski with Jake, Jarek, and kind of Sergio. 4 full laps and some other skiing to round out the total. Pretty relaxed on the flats and downhills, but we pushed a few uphills. Sergio is looking surprisingly good for his 7th time on skis. Some of the best conditions of the year.
Super cold. Up 28th to franklin bridge, then lake, and home.
Jogging around the indoor track with Sergio. Tossed a disk with a few people after.
Run to school.Into the wind the whole way.
With Jake at Hyland. Snow was fairly snow. I was having trouble balancing in the V2. I'm hoping it was just tired legs from squats.

Ran to my ultimate game. Played for 40 minutes and ran back. My team is so bad. Picture college XC ultimate, but where half your team is slow and fat. Also, your team doesn't have Brett, Taylor, or Carter so nobody can throw.
Run to PT. Doc said I need to improve my flexibility and hip strength. No surprises there, but I'm hoping that working with someone will help get everything in working order.

With Jake for the first 5. Lake bridge to franklin bridge. Commented that it felt really warm. It turned out to be 18 degrees. Jake and I hit pretty good paces on the east bank. Knee started to bother me a little in the last half mile.

Department across ped bridge to lake bridge and home. Felt pretty good, but I wasn't dressed well for the run. I wasn't planning on running home so I threw on whatever was lying around my office. No knee pain.
With Jake and Keiser for the first 5. Good pace on a cold windy day. Stretches and some hip exercises after.

With the Run N Fun group. Dropped back with Barret(?) . We ran Lillydale in reverse which was weird starting out. Felt fine. There Tuesday runs are really good at getting me back in shape. Longer and quicker than what I do on my own.

1.5 mile warmup

4 mile tempo in 23:30

2.5 mile cooldown

Felt file on this run. The mile splits were pretty consistent and I was only really struggling at the end. The goal is to do this workout longer or faster every week. We'll see how that goes...

Garmin didn't start at the beginning so I'm guessing a little. Ran with Jake which helps keep the pace honest. We did the normal Lake to Ford loop with the trails on the west side of the river.Achilles still sore and slight knee tendonitis.

Road with the Dunn Early crew for the first time. They were doing the Fulton Gran Fondo which is a 100 mile ride and biking 15 miles to get there. So we biked to the start of the ride in a pack around 18mph average. Then waited around for a half hour for the ride to start and took off with 1200 other people on a ride. It was pretty crazy to be biking in a group that bike. I just stayed to the outside and tried not to hit anyone. There were only a few times where I had to come to a stop but then we got on the greenway and could open up a bit. 

It was tough to decide when to turn around because I was in a pack so it was pretty easy to keep up, but I knew the way back would be more tiring. Ended up turning around a little earlier than I needed to because I was still able to PR on the Sabo Bridge Climb a mile from home.

Ran with Jake. 
32nd - Longfellow Ave, Creek Trail, 55, 32nd

Felt pretty good once my legs loosened up. Was holding 7 min pace even after Jake turned off to add on. Lunges and B skips after with a few squats.
Morning run with Jake. I don't remember exactly how far or what pace. I can check strava if I ever really care. Pretty tired since my 7 day total is in the high 30s.

In honor of the TC mile which Gjoraas and Petro are running I decided to do a mile hard. It was supposed to be 2x1 but after 5 minutes rest I wasn't ready to do a second. 5:05 for the mile on dirt in trainers. That means I'm high 40s or low 50s right now. Then 3 by 400 in 72 pace. Trying to get a little more intensity in my running to help lose the weight and get some turnover back.
